ions The term Pacific Islands generally excludes the islands of New Zealand and the continent of Australia The indigenous Māori of New Zealand are a Polynesian people Historically the region was called Australasia although this often meant just Australia New Zealand and sometimes Papua New Guinea The term gives special emphasis to Australia and is falling out of favour The countries are listed below according to their UN classification KategoriyaLists of countriesContinents list of countries by
